cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with synthesizing facial affect using a 3D Morphable Model and image processing techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper involves training Deep Neural Networks for affect recognition using synthesized images. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves using machine learning techniques for data augmentation and affect recognition. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with generating image sequences of affect. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper involves generating realistic facial expressions for affect analysis, which has applications in human-computer interaction.
